task.name: Deterministic Report Generator
task.prompt: Write a public function named GenerateReport that takes a string 'title' and a long 'timestamp' (Unix epoch milliseconds), and returns a formatted report string. The timestamp MUST come from the parameter, not from DateTime.Now. The function must be deterministic - same inputs always produce same output. Return format: "Report: {title} (Generated: {timestamp})"

bugPrevention.realWorldBug: Report timestamps differ between test runs, breaking snapshot tests
bugPrevention.calorApproach: Pure effect signature prevents time effects
bugPrevention.csharpApproach: Passing timestamp as parameter (DI pattern)

task.name: Seeded Random Selection
task.prompt: Write a public function named SelectItem that takes an integer array 'items' and an integer 'seed', and returns one item selected using the seed for randomization. The selection must be deterministic - same seed always selects same item. Use simple modulo: seed % length gives the index.

bugPrevention.realWorldBug: Tests randomly fail because item selection varies between runs
bugPrevention.calorApproach: Pure effect signature prevents rand effects
bugPrevention.csharpApproach: Using seeded Random instance from parameter

task.name: Deterministic ID Generator

task.name: Deterministic Shuffle
task.prompt: Write a public function named ShuffleArray that takes an integer array 'items' and an integer 'seed', and returns a new shuffled array. The shuffle must be deterministic - same seed always produces same order. Do not modify the original array. Use Fisher-Yates shuffle with LCG: rng = rng * 1103515245 + 12345, index = abs(rng) % (j+1).

bugPrevention.realWorldBug: Shuffle order changes between test runs, breaking order-dependent assertions
bugPrevention.calorApproach: Pure effect signature, seed-based randomization
bugPrevention.csharpApproach: Seeded Random instance for deterministic shuffle
